Specificity :
In css conflict resolution Specificity is a mechanism to find out the most specific rule for the element which has encountered conflicting rules.

four components of specificity:
1: style attribute in element 
2: id attribute in css rule
3. class,pseudo class, attribute in css rule
4. number of elements in the rule

Each of the above four components (except # of elements - it can have value == number of elements) have either "0" or "1" as permitted values

Example:

p.highlight{
	color: green;
}

A.SPECIFICITY: 0-0-1-1
p{
	color:red;
}

B.SPECIFICITY: 0-0-0-1

so A wins